  "description": [
    "6S IMPORTANT TRADE CONDITIONS FAVOR WEEKS STOCK MART Movement of Prices Only Mi nor ReflectionNew Bond Financing By W 8 COUSINS NEW YORK Jan 27Domestic economic and business developments during the past week were much more favorable than the movements of prices on the stock market would seem to indicate Only in the last two full sessions of the week was trading in specula tive stocks anything like normal while on Tuesday the aggregate trading was the smallest for a sin gle session since November Specta cular features were few in number and the general trend of the old line market favorites was upward In the action of the stock market especially in the latter part of the week there was every indication of a return of popular favor to the railroad stocks The incentive is more than the favorable earnings statements for 1922 which have been finding their way into the press THE BOND MARKET While the offering of new bonds during the past week made a sharp drop from those of the preceding three weeks of the New Year the aggregate was well up to the av erage of the last six months The most prominent new issues"
